    <fr:p>We first prove (a).
      By replacing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> by a finite étale cover, if necessary, we can reduce to the case where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G=G^0]]></fr:tex>.
      By (iii) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.5" href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.5.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="4.2.5" />, the local system <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}^nf_*\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> underlies an algebraic family <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> of Hodge structures, and so we can apply <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.8" href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.8.xml" taxon="Corollary" number="4.2.8" /> (by (i) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.5" href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.5.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="4.2.5" />).
      The group <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> is reductive, since it admits a faithful semi-simple representation (namely <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R}^nf_*\mathbb {C})_s]]></fr:tex>).
      If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> (which we assume to be connected) were not semi-simple, then it would admit a non-trivial complex representation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex> of rank <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex>;
      since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H_s]]></fr:tex> is faithful, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex> would then be a direct factor of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[((H+H^*)_\mathbb {C}^{\otimes  m})_s]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex>.
      But this would contradict (iii.b) of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.8" href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.8.xml" taxon="Corollary" number="4.2.8" />, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(H+H^*)^{\otimes  m}]]></fr:tex> is algebraic, and no tensor power of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\rho ]]></fr:tex> is trivial.</fr:p>
